article.headline: Md.-Eastern Shore 73, N.C. Central 58
article.story: DURHAM, N.C. -- Neal Pitt scored 24 points to lead Maryland-Eastern Shore to a 73-58 win over North Carolina Central on Wednesday night. The Hawks (4-11) snapped a two-game losing streak with the nonconference victory. The Eagles (2-20) have now lost two in a row after winning two consecutive games for their only victories of the season. Maryland-Eastern Shore led by as many as 21 points in the first half and 31-18 at halftime. N.C. Central closed to 59-52 with 4:43 left, but could get no closer. The Eagles outrebounded Maryland-Eastern Shore 36-35, but committed 20 turnovers to the Hawks' 12. Jamie Boyer and Josh Bright scored 14 points apiece for Maryland-Eastern Shore, and Gary Lee had 10. Bryan Ayala led N.C. Central with 19 points and seven rebounds -- all defensive -- and Vincent Davis had 17 points and six rebounds.
